file_name: File:Victoria Onetto en la Puesta en marcha del Centro Cultural Kirchner.jpg
parsed caption:
Buenos Aires, 21 de mayo de 2015 – En el marco de las celebraciones por un
nuevo aniversario de la Revolución de Mayo, bajo el lema “El mismo Sol, la
misma Patria”, la presidenta de la Nación, Cristina Fernández de Kirchner,
puso en funcionamiento el Centro Cultural Kirchner en el histórico Palacio de
Correos.

Del acto participaron, la ministra de Cultura de la Nación; Teresa Parodi y el

parsed caption:
An astronaut aboard the International Space Station used a very long lens to
shoot this detailed photograph of the northern tip of Cape Cod, showing 14
kilometers (8.5 miles) of its 105-kilometer (65-mile) length. Cape Cod is one
of the biggest barrier islands in the world, and it protects towns like
Provincetown and its harbor from storm waves coming in from the Atlantic
Ocean. It thus also protects the southeastern Massachusetts coastline.

In the photo, the cream-colored features are symmetrically shaped dunes built
mainly by northeasterly winter winds. On the water, the white streaks are
boats and their wakes.

Why is Cape Cod shaped the way it is? When the glaciers were at their fullest
extent, sea level was more than one hundred meters (325 feet) lower than it is
today because so much water was bound up in huge continental ice sheets. As
the ice melted, sea level kept rising and areas that had been covered by ice
were submerged under the rising Atlantic waters. At this point waves and sea
currents started to erode the moraines and river deposits of the cape.

Because it juts into the Atlantic Ocean, the cape shoreline is heavily eroded
by waves. Sometimes the ocean breaks through the barrier island, as happened
during Hurricane Bob in 1991. But even without major storms, strong wave
erosion smoothes and disrupts the beachline facing the Atlantic Ocean.

In this photo, the sands eroded by the waves are swept northward to feed the
growth around Provincetown. When a sandy coastal spit like Cape Cod advances
into deeper water, it grows more slowly and wave action starts to bend the
line of spit growth inshore. In the case of Cape Cod, this wave refraction
around the tip has turned the growth direction progressively to the west and
then to the south, forming the hook shape we see today.

parsed caption:
23.09.2009 01445 Radebeul-Hoflößnitz, Knohllweg 37: Schloß Hoflößnitz (GMP:
51.111539,13.662244). Auf dem Gebiet des 1401 von Meißens Markgrafen gekauften
burggräflichen dohnaischen Weinberg entstand das Lust- und Berghaus
Hoflößnitz. Ursprünglich nur aus Preßhaus und Verwalterwohnung bestehen, baute
es Ezechiel Eckhardt im Auftrag des Kurfüsten Johann Georg I. (1585-1656) zum
fürstlichen Wohnhaus für die Tage der Weinlese aus. Sein Obergeschoß
beherbergt den großen Festsaal, dessen Holzbalkendecke mit 80 rechteckigen,
vom Hofmaler Albert Eyckhout gezeichneten Leinwandbildern brasilianischer
Vögel ausgefüllt ist. Wandbilder wiederum verkünden in ernster und heiterer
Art Lebensweisheiten. Der 1409 bezeugte "weyngarten, der do heysst auff der
Lessenitz" wurde wiederholt durch Grundstückszukäufe erweitert, bis ein
geschlossenes, die Lößnitzhänge bedeckendes Weinbaugebiet beisammen war. Den
größten Umfang erreichte der kurfürstliche Besitz in der Mitte des 18.
Jahrhunderts. Sicht von Süden. Im Hintergrund Bismarckturm und Spitzhaus.

Auf dem Gebiet des 1401 von Meißens Markgrafen gekauften burggräflichen dohnaischen Weinberg entstand das Lust- und Berghaus Hoflößnitz. Ursprünglich nur aus Preßhaus und Verwalterwohnung bestehen, baute es Ezechiel Eckhardt im Auftrag des Kurfüsten Johann Georg I. (1585-1656) zum fürstlichen Wohnhaus für die Tage der Weinlese aus. Sein Obergeschoß beherbergt den großen Festsaal, dessen Holzbalkendecke mit 80 rechteckigen, vom Hofmaler Albert Eyckhout gezeichneten Leinwandbildern brasilianischer Vögel ausgefüllt ist. Wandbilder wiederum verkünden in ernster und heiterer Art Lebensweisheiten. Der 1409 bezeugte "weyngarten, der do heysst auff der Lessenitz" wurde wiederholt durch Grundstückszukäufe erweitert, bis ein geschlossenes, die Lößnitzhänge bedeckendes Weinbaugebiet beisammen war. Den größten Umfang erreichte der kurfürstliche Besitz in der Mitte des 18. Jahrhunderts. Sicht von Süden. Im Hintergrund Bismarckturm und Spitzhaus. servicios de guardia esta Nochebuena y les ha felicitado y agradecido su labor
desde sus respectivas emisoras.

description: ['star at the centre of the Solar System']
parsed caption:
AIA 0335 channel (as well as AIA 211) highlights the active region of the
outer atmosphere of the Sun - the corona. Active regions, solar flares, and
coronal mass ejections will appear bright here. The dark areas - or coronal
holes - are places where very little radiation is emitted, yet are the main
source of solar wind particles.

**Where:** Active regions of the corona

**Wavelength:** 335 angstroms (0.0000000335 m) = Extreme Ultraviolet

**Primary ions seen:** 15 times ionized iron (Fe XVI)

**Characteristic temperature:** 2.8 million K (5 million F)

parsed caption:
24.06.2004 17089 Klempenow (Breest): Burg Klempenow (GMP: 53.790586,13.311360)
aus der Zeit der deutschen Besiedlung. Um 1240 trat der pommersche Herzog
Wartislaw III. in Erscheinung, und die Burg Klempenow geht vermutlich auf ihn
zurück. 1331 wird die Burg urkundlich erwähnt. Die Burg wurde immer wieder
erweitert, teilweise zerstört und wieder aufgebaut. Die heute ältesten
Bestandteile der Burg sind der Turm und die Wehrmauer, die aus der Mitte bis
zum Ende des 13. Jahrhunderts nachgewiesen werden können. Das letzte Mal wurde
sie wohl 1697 instand gesetzt. In der Mitte des 18. Jahrhunderts erfolgte noch
ein Umbau zur Erweiterung des Kornspeichers und 1820 erhielt sie dann ihre
heutige Form. Bis in die 1990er Jahre diente Burg Klempenow als Wohnhaus. Seit
1998 kann die Burg besichtigt werden.

file_name: File:Prominent Native American chefs gathered at USDA to prepare Indigenous cuisine for the White House Tribal Nations Summit on 5 December 2023 - 22.jpg
parsed caption:
This week, prominent Native American chefs gathered at USDA to prepare
Indigenous cuisine for the White House Tribal Nations Summit (Dec. 6-7) and
related events. This year’s White House Summit highlights Native American
foods, and USDA is empowering Indigenous foodways and food sovereignty through
new programs and resources. The chefs are joined by students and faculty from
the Southwestern Polytechnical Institute (SIPI) Tribal College Culinary
Program. Together, they prepared meals that center Indigenous ingredients and
foodways, including smoked salmon with a foraged vinaigrette of cedar, spruce,
rose, labrador tea; bison tepary bean chili; smoked fish, squash, and
cranberry soup; and turkey roulade with wild rice. All dishes feature tribally
produced ingredients.

The chefs included: Rob Kinneen Tlingit (Alaska), Lead Chef, North American
Traditional Indigenous Food Systems (NĀTIFS); Crystal Wapepah (Kickapoo and
Sac & Fox Tribes), Joe Robbins, Penobscot, (Maine); Fransisco Algeria,
Menominee, (Wisconsin), and Leah Husby, Menominee, (Wisconsin).

They were joined by students and faculty from the culinary program at
Southwestern Polytechnical Institute (SIPI) in Albuquerque N.M.: Leonard
Bailey, Chef instructor, Rebecca Lee (Yupik Athabaskan/White Mountain Apache),
Educator Technician Tutor; Bilhiigibaa “Billy” Vigil (Navajo/Acoma
Pueblo/Oglala Sioux) Aysa Norberto (Navajo); Summer Hornbek (Kickapoo/Navajo);
Lynette Pradt (Laguna Pueblo/Winnebago); and Benjamin Romero (Taos Pueblo)
(USDA photo by Tom Witham)

parsed caption:
Signal B259 at the north end of platform 1 at [Filton Abbey Wood railway
station](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Filton_Abbey_Wood_railway_station
"w:Filton Abbey Wood railway station"). This seems to be exclusively a wrong-
line signal, as trains normally pass southbound on this line and as such
arrive at the back of this signal. The two junction indicators show there
there are three possible routes north of this signal, with no inidcator the
route is set to continue on the wrong-road northbound. With the 45° indicator
set, the train will head towards [Bristol
Parkway](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bristol_Parkway_railway_station
"w:Bristol Parkway railway station") but on the correct line; the 90°
indicator shows that the route is set for the train to continue over the
northbound line to Bristol Parkway onto the line towards [South
Wales](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/South_Wales "w:South Wales").

parsed caption:
[Hunt-Morgan House](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/en:Hunt-Morgan_House
"w:en:Hunt-Morgan House"), located in the Gratz Park Historic District in
[Lexington, Kentucky](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/en:Lexington,_Kentucky
"w:en:Lexington, Kentucky"), was built by [John Wesley
Hunt](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/en:John_Wesley_Hunt "w:en:John Wesley
Hunt") in 1814. Other famous residents include Confederate [General John Hunt
Morgan](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/en:John_Hunt_Morgan "w:en:John Hunt
Morgan") and Noble Prize recipient [Dr. Thomas Hunt
Morgan](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/en:Thomas_Hunt_Morgan "w:en:Thomas Hunt
Morgan"). The current address is 201 N. Mill Street, Lexington, Kentucky.

description: ['star at the centre of the Solar System']
parsed caption:
AIA 0335 channel (as well as AIA 211) highlights the active region of the
outer atmosphere of the Sun - the corona. Active regions, solar flares, and
coronal mass ejections will appear bright here. The dark areas - or coronal
holes - are places where very little radiation is emitted, yet are the main
source of solar wind particles.

**Where:** Active regions of the corona

**Wavelength:** 335 angstroms (0.0000000335 m) = Extreme Ultraviolet

**Primary ions seen:** 15 times ionized iron (Fe XVI)

**Characteristic temperature:** 2.8 million K (5 million F)

parsed caption:
Great Central Railway Winter Gala 2012 The BR Standard Class 2 2-6-0 is a
class of steam locomotive, one of the British Railways Standard classes of the
1950s. They were physically the smallest of the Standard classes; 65 were
built.

The design was derived from the Ivatt-designed LMS Class 2MT 2-6-0, with a
reduced cab to enable it to fit into a universal loading gauge, and other
standard fittings, most notably a taller chimney, others including the lack of
an Ivatt dome and side plates connecting the two sections of the engine.

parsed caption:
AIA 1700 channel (as well as AIA 1600) often shows a web-like pattern of
bright areas that highlight places where bundles of magnetic fields lines are
concentrated. However, small areas with a lot of field lines will appear
black, usually near sunspots and active regions.

**Where:** Temperature minimum and photosphere

**Wavelength:** 1700 angstroms (0.00000017 m) = Far Ultraviolet

**Primary ions seen:** Continuum

**Characteristic temperature:** 6,000 K (11,000 F)

description: ['star at the centre of the Solar System']
parsed caption:
AIA 0171 channel is especially good at showing coronal loops - the arcs
extending off of the Sun where plasma moves along magnetic field lines. The
brightest spots seen here are locations where the magnetic field near the
surface is exceptionally strong.

**Where:** Quiet corona and upper transition region

**Wavelength:** 171 angstroms (0.0000000171 m) = Extreme Ultraviolet

**Primary ions seen:** 8 times ionized iron (Fe IX)

**Characteristic temperature:** 1 million K (1.8 million F)

description: ['church building with cemetery in Fischlham, Upper Austria']

15th century. It is shifted to the south in relation to the longitudinal axis
of the nave.

description: [None, None, 'building near a railway track that contains the controls to operate signals and points and other equipment used to regulate the movement of trains']
parsed caption:
Nordwärts, die beiden Gleise links sind die Strecke
[6420](https://de.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bahnstrecke_K%C3%B6then%E2%80%93Aschersleben
"de:Bahnstrecke Köthen–Aschersleben") von Aschersleben, das mit Fahrleitung
überspannte in Bildmitte ist ein Bahnhofsgleis, das am Stellwerk 4 in die
Streckengleise daneben mündet. Die beiden Vorsignalwiederholer entsprchen der
zum Aufnahmezeitpunkt neuesten Siemens-Bauform mit LED-Lichtpunkten und
Zusatzanzeigern. Im Hintergrund steht das
[elektromechanische](https://de.wikipedia.org/wiki/elektromechanisches_Stellwerk
"de:elektromechanisches Stellwerk") Stellwerk 3, Bauform S&H 1912.

parsed caption:
Historischer, dreiseitiger Grenzstein "Dreimärker" mit den Buchstaben M für
[Michelbach](https://de.wikipedia.org/wiki/Michelbach_\(Marburg\)
"de:Michelbach \(Marburg\)"), K für
[Caldern](https://de.wikipedia.org/wiki/Caldern "de:Caldern") und A für
[Elnhausen](https://de.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elnhausen "de:Elnhausen"), das 1577
noch Ailnhausen geschrieben wurde. Lage: An einer Wegekreuzung auf dem
[Hungert](https://de.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hungert "de:Hungert") an der
Gemarkungsgrenze zwischen Michelbach (Flur 14), Caldern (Flur 10) und
Elnhausen (Flur 3). Ansicht der Elnhäuser Seite, die jedoch vom Steinmetz mit
der Calderner Seite verwechselt wurde.

file_name: File:The Control of Trade in Endangered Species (Fees) Regulations 2009 (UKSI 2009-496 qp).pdf
depicts: ['The Control of Trade in Endangered Species (Fees) Regulations 2009']
parsed caption:
These Regulations specify fees which are payable to the Secretary of State in
relation to applications for certain permits and certificates specified in
Council Regulation (EC) No. 338-97 (OJ No. L61, 3.3.97, p. 1) (“the Council
Regulation”), which relates to the protection of species of wild fauna and
flora, and Commission Regulation (EC) No. 865-06 (OJ No. L166, 19.6.06, p. 1),
which provides further details in connection with the regime set out in the
Council Regulation. Those Regulations apply the Convention on International
Trade in Endangered Species of Wild Fauna and Flora (ratified by the United
Kingdom on 2nd August 1976). The issue of such permits or certificates allows
certain trading or other activities in relation to specimens (animals or
plants, or parts or derivatives of animals or plants) which are included in a
relevant Annex to the Council Regulation.

file_name: File:The Aviva Stadium - Lansdowne Road, Dublin (5436344013).jpg
parsed caption:
The Aviva Stadium - Lansdowne Road, Dublin

This attractive stadium is built on the site of the old Lansdowne Road venue,
which was demolished in 2007, and replaces that stadium as home to the Irish
rugby union team and the Republic of Ireland national football team (soccer).

The stadium's roof is designed to undulate in a wave-like manner so as to
avoid blocking light to local residences.

The stadium was officially opened on 14 May 2010 but I have not had the
opportunity to see the inside of it until today.

The stadium has four tiers, with the lower and upper tiers being for general
access, the second tier for premium tickets and the third tier for corporate
boxes. The north stand, however, is single tiered due to its proximity to
local housing. The premium level holds 11,000 spectators, while the box level
holds 1,300. The remaining 38,700 seats are shared between the top and bottom
tiers. The capacity of the stadium was criticised even before its opening for
being too small, particularly in light of the large supporter attendance
figures for Irish rugby internationals and soccer internationals at Croke Park
since 2007. American Football In 2012, Aviva Stadium will host an American
college football match billed as the Emerald Isle Classic between the Notre
Dame Fighting Irish and the Navy Midshipmen.

[streetsofdublin.com](http://streetsofdublin.com)

parsed caption:
The Lotus Seven is a small, lightweight 2 seat open sports car. The Series 2
was built from 1961-67 1957 Series 1; 1172cc 4 cyl. Ford Side-valve, Aluminium
Shell 1960 Series 2; 1340cc 4 cyl. OHV Kent 1968 Series 3; 1500cc 4 cyl. OHV
Kent, Large 7 in the grille 1970 Series 4; 1700cc 4 cyl. New shape and
fibreglass shell

After Lotus ended production of the Seven, Caterham bought the rights and
today Caterham make both kits and fully assembled cars based on the original
design.

file_name: File:Transhumance moutons chèvres Lille 19 mai 2019 c 13.jpg
description: ['periodic migration of livestock between winter and summer pastures', 'city and commune in Nord, Hauts-de-France, Northern France', 'domesticated ruminant bred for meat, wool, and milk']
parsed caption:
In the context of the management of urban green spaces by ecopaturing ([ Urban
Ecopastoralisme](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/en:_Ecopastoralisme_urbain
"w:en: Ecopastoralisme urbain")) in 2019, the city of Lille uses 140 sheep and
10 goats, in the wood of the citadel, around the Citadel of Vauban in Lille,
under the Royal Gate of the Bouflers Barracks and in several other urban green
spaces. On Sunday 19 May 2019, an urban transhumance took place between the
Citadelle wood and the Marcel Dhénin urban farm for a part of the animals
(animals belonging to the company Ecozoone specialized in fixed or itinerant
grazing, with in this case a " shepherdess "his assistants and his dogs).
These herbivores maintain vegetation in a more environmentally friendly way
than when they are mowed or machine-cut (eg goats stand up and eat the low
leaves of bushes and trees, and sheep graze by better accompanying the soil,
enriched by their excrement) and during itineraries they play a role of
"walking biological corridor", because moving from one site to another, they
carry propagules of plants and other organisms such as as mushroom spores,
propagules of lichens, insects and other invertebrates, bacteria, etc. (The
herbivores carry these propagules under their hooves, in their coat but also
in their digestive tract.Some seeds will germinate or take root only after
having passed into the digestive tract of an herbivore). These traveling
animals reconnect relict, fragmented and distant natural semi-ecological
environments, contributing to the ecological connectivity essential for
maintaining biodiversity.

If the work is a derivative work or a compilation incorporating previously published material, the year date of first publication of the derivative work or compilation is sufficient. file_name: File:Last Address sign - Moscow, Pokrovka Street, 31 (2020-02-16) 18.jpg
parsed caption:
The Last Address Sign is a commemorative plaque that is installed on the last
known residential address of victims of the Soviet Union's Communist regime.
The memorial sign is a small, 11x19 cm stainless steel plaque that contains
information about the repressed person. This information usually contains his
or her name, profession, date of birth, date of arrest, date and reason of
death (was shot or died in a Soviet concentration camp), and date of
rehabilitation ('for lack of corpus delicti').

[Bakenesserkerk](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bakenesserkerk
"en:Bakenesserkerk") is visible.

description: ['tram system in Leipzig', "Central railway terminus of Leipzig, Germany. Europe's largest railway station at 83,460 Square meters with 26 platforms.", '1967 Czechoslovakian tram']
parsed caption:
Der Zug der Linie 1 fährt nach Lausen, in Normalfall wäre es die falsche
Richtung. Die Linien 1 und 3 sind allerdings von den Sperrungen und
Umleitungen besonders betroffen. Der Zug kommt von der Berliner Brücke, fährt
eine Dreiviertelrunde um den Ring bis zum Westplatz und von dort nach Lausen.  
Diese Stelle ist eine der schon regelrecht berüchtigten Wartepositionen, es
gibt im Bereich des Innenstadtringes keinerlei Straßenbahnbevorrechtigung. Die
Schaltzeiten sind auf den Kraftverkehr abgestimmt, durch die Haltezeiten
entsteht für den öffentlichen Nahverkehr eine sehr effektive rote Welle.

file_name: File:Desfile de Carnaval em São Vicente, Madeira - 2020-02-23 - IMG 5352.jpg
depicts: ['2020 Carnival parade in São Vicente, Madeira']
parsed caption:
Carnival parade in São Vicente, Madeira, a few days before the lockdown of the
Covid-19 pandemic was declared. The parade was composed mainly of children and
elderly people belonging to various schools and institutions of the parish.
Among the troupes were the "Super Grandmas of Adenorama", the "Senior Prisonal
Institute", "Sea to Sea", and "Rock and Roll Has No Age", among others.

**Dtsch.-Sowjet. Grenz- u. Freundschaftsvertrag**

Scherl: Die Unterzeichnung in Moskau. Als Ergebnis der Moskauer Besprechungen
wurde vom Reichsminister des Auswärtigen v. Ribbentrop und vom Vorsitzenden
des Rates der Volkskommissare und Außenkommissar Molotow im Kreml eine
gemeinsame politische Erklärung und der Freundschaftsvertrag zwischen der
Reichsregierung und der Regierung der UdSSR unterzeichnet. Unser Bild zeigt
Reichsaußenminister v. Ribbentrop während der Unterzeichnung. Links neben ihm
der sowjetrussische Botschafter in Berlin Schkarzew; dahinter (von rechts)
Stalin, Außenkommissar Molotow und der Generalstabschef der sowjetrussischen
Armee Stapostnikow. ADN-ZB/Archiv Sowjetunion, September 1939 In Moskau wird
am 28.9.1939 zwischen dem Deutschen Reich und der UdSSR ein Grenz- und
Freundschaftsvertrag sowie eine gemeinsame politische Erklärung unterzeichnet.
Der deutsche Reichsaußenminister Joachim von Ribbentrop während der
Unterzeichnung; stehend v.r. J. W. Stalin, der Vorsitzende des Rates der
Volkskommissare W. M. Molotow, der sowjetische Botschafter in Berlin
Schkwarzew und der sowjetische Generalstabschef B. M. Schaposchnikow. 11983-39

**Abgebildete Personen:**

  * Ribbentrop, Joachim von: Außenminister, NSDAP, Deutschland
  * [Molotow, Wjatscheslaw Michailowitsch](https://de.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wjatscheslaw_Michailowitsch_Molotow "de:Wjatscheslaw Michailowitsch Molotow"): Außenminister, Sowjetunion ([GND](//commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Commons:GND "Commons:GND") [11873461X](http://d-nb.info/gnd/11873461X))
  * Schkwarzew, Alexander: Botschafter in Deutschland, Sowjetunion
  * [Schaposchnikow, Boris](https://de.wikipedia.org/wiki/Boris_Michailowitsch_Schaposchnikow "de:Boris Michailowitsch Schaposchnikow"): Marschall, Sowjetunion ([GND](//commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Commons:GND "Commons:GND") [11882600X](http://d-nb.info/gnd/11882600X))
  * [Stalin, Josef W.](https://de.wikipedia.org/wiki/Josef_Stalin "de:Josef Stalin"): 1878-1953; Marschall, Vorsitzender des Ministerrates, Generalsekretär der KP, Sowjetunion ([GND](//commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Commons:GND "Commons:GND") [118642499](http://d-nb.info/gnd/118642499))
